Articles.Content:
hey, I wanted to start a plane yesterday and for some reason it didn't lift up. after some experimenting I realized that for some reason there was no lifting force. I tried some other parts and some modded canards and winglets still had some hadn't,  from very different mods, so it could be ruled out that one mod is blocking the others. So I thought that the installation of one of the mods for some reason broke and I first tried to reinstall the mods (where other problems arose but nothing unusual while installing, like a mod which caused a stuck on load bug). So I deinstalled everything, including ksp, reinstalled it, threw some mods out I never used or were more a liability than help, and restarted my save. I realized that amost none of my vessels worked anymore duw to missing parts but since it's a fairly new save I got none in space so this is annoying but expected.

But the main question was: is the lifting force-bug still there? And yes, yes it is.

Since my modlist is still extremely long: Does anyone know a mod which could cause this problem?
